I think of a dream where I went to train tracks and saw a girl laying there. I've been leaning towards laying on train tracks. I'm thinking of the best way to lay and make sure I die. I used to like Christian Gates' part, now I hear it and think it's all bullshit. I hate it. I hate this song. I hate being so angry. Anger is my only form of therapy now. I hate it. I'm just tired of crying, and I can't smile anymore. I know clench a fist when I see those who hurt me. I used to cry, break down, and hide from everyone. Now I see them and clench a fist. I see them and feel so angry. I've avoided hate for so long, but it's becoming so hard. I just want them to treat me nice. I just want to be heard. I just want help when I cry. I just want help when I have a panic attack. I just want to be appreciated. I just want someone to read my writing and say I'm talented. I want someone to say I'm not ugly. I want someone to hug me. I miss being held. My mother never held me, and my father left my life at a young age. My family hated me from birth. I grew to hate love. Avoid attachment, avoid hugs, and avoid comfort. I was alone, and I told myself I was happy. Then I met someone who held me. Who would hold me when I had a panic attack. Who would kiss me even when I fucked up. I fucked up without thinking and they would still comfort me and let me apologize and try to fix things. Then they left. It's so cheesy. I probably seem retarded or something like it. I just enjoyed comfort. I enjoyed that for the first time in my life. I wasn't alone. Now, whenever I see them, I feel angry. My friends abandon me when I start to break down. I tried talking to them, they thought I was just seeking attention. I hate them. I hate everyone. I hate myself. I want to die. I've wanted to die what feels like my whole life. Yet I still haven't killed myself. I want to. I plan to. I don't need a note. No one cares. I just need to lay and let that damn train hit me. If you read all of this. You wasted a bit of your life. Like how I wasted mine typing this. I wish you the best, though. I hope you at least enjoyed reading my life. Here's a poem I wrote.  You look to the blade.  You wish to write your message with that familiar crimson color.  You wish to paint with that familiar red.  You want to pick up the blade.  But you look and see a pen.  A pen with black ink.  You wish to use the vibrant crimson color.  The glowing, undeniable crimson.  Instead you pick up the pen.  You write with the black ink and be vibrant with words.  Your words matter far more than how the words are shown.  If your words are shown.  Some words don't need to be shown.  Some words are for you.  You'll write and write.  You'll make mistakes.  But you'll write.  Maybe you'll reread.  Maybe you'll just write.  Maybe you'll write one day.  But the next you'll go back to the blade. But you must grab the pen.  Write.  Write & write.  Write not until your heart stops, but until your smile starts.   Do you like my writing? I know you don't, don't worry. Goodnight, whoever reads this. I hope you live a nice, long life.
